# TypeScript Types Guide

## Core User Types

### User Role Enumeration
```typescript
type UserRole = 'admin' | 'pentester' | 'client';
```

### User Interface
The main user interface should include:
```typescript
interface User {
  _id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  role: UserRole;
  // Additional user properties
}
```

## Entity Types

### Vulnerability Interface
Key vulnerability properties from [FormPreview component](mdc:src/components/vulenerabilityReports/subcomponents/FormPreview.tsx):
```typescript
interface Vulnerability {
  _id: string;
  title: string;
  severity: string;
  status: string;
  description: string;
  affected_host: string;
  steps_to_reproduce: string;
  recommended_solution: string;
  impact: string;
  likelihood: string;
  cvss: number;
  cvssVector: string;
  attachments: Attachment[];
  comments: Comment[];
  reporter: User;
  hasJiraIntegration: boolean;
}
```

### Pentest Interface
```typescript
interface Pentest {
  _id: string;
  title: string;
  status: string;
  clients: Client[];
  // Additional pentest properties
}
```

### Client Interface
```typescript
interface Client {
  _id: string;
  name: string;
  logoUrl?: string;
  // Additional client properties
}
```

## Component Props Types

### Navigation Types
```typescript
type NavItem = {
  title: string;
  href: string;
  icon: string | React.ReactNode;
  subItems?: NavItem[];
};
```

### Status Types
```typescript
interface StatusOption {
  value: string;
  label: string;
  color: string;
  textColor: string;
}
```

## Hook Return Types

### useUser Hook Return Type
```typescript
interface UseUserReturn {
  user: User | null;
  role: UserRole | null;
  loading: boolean;
  isAdmin: () => boolean;
  isPentester: () => boolean;
  isClient: () => boolean;
}
```

## Type Import Patterns
- Import types from [types.ts](mdc:src/types/types.ts)
- Use consistent interface naming (PascalCase)
- Export types that are used across multiple components
- Use generic types for API responses when appropriate

## Type Safety Best Practices
- Always type API responses
- Use optional chaining for nested properties
- Implement proper loading state handling
- Use type guards for role checking
